column2:
ALOW (Adolescent Lead Our World) - The idea is to create a “safe and protective environment” for adolescents and children — giving them access to education, awareness, opportunities, and a supportive community.

Models under ALOW:

1. Education (Life skills, adolescent rights, 100% enrollment up to HSC, play for peace, education supports, career guidance); 

2. Health (SRHR-Sexual Reproductive Health Rights, anemic camps, Bio Intensive Gardening (BIG), mental health support; 

3. Child Protection (strengthening Village, Panchayat, Block and District level child protection committees, Tracking records for migration, placing demands to concern authorities, Child Friendly Accountable mechanism (CFAM), Right to Education Act, Child marriage prohibition Act, Interface meetings; 

4. Stengthening Community based Organization with gender aspects (Adolescent Girls Clubs, Community Support Groups (CSG), School Management Committee (SMC), parents committee.
